  = studio\n | single1     = There You Go\n | single1date = November 21, 1956\n | single2     = Next in Line\n | single2date = April 15, 1957\n | single3     = [[Home of the Blues]]\n | single3date = August 10, 1957\n | single4     = [[Ballad of a Teenage Queen]]\n | single4date = December 1, 1957\n | single5     = [[Guess Things Happen That Way]]\n | single5date = May 20, 1958\n | single6     = The Ways of a Woman in Love\n | single6date = August 11, 1958\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}} [{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r105775|pure_url=yes}} link]\n| rev2      = \n| rev2Score = \n}}\n\n'''''Johnny Cash Sings the Songs That Made Him Famous''''' is the third [[studio album]] by American singer-songwriter [[Johnny Cash]]. It was originally released on 13 November 1958, but later re-issued in 2003, under the label [[Var\u00e8se Sarabande]], with four different versions of tracks already present on the original LP as a bonus. The complete contents of the album are also incorporated into an extended version of the previous collection ''[[With His Hot and Blue Guitar]]'' included in the 2012 box set ''[[Johnny Cash: The Complete Columbia Album Collection]]''.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| total_length = 28:57\n\n| title1 = [[Ballad of a Teenage Queen]]\n| writer1 = [[Jack Clement]]\n| length1 = 2:13\n\n| title2 = There You Go\n| writer2 = [[Johnny Cash]]\n| length2 = 2:19\n\n| title3 = [[I Walk the Line]]\n| writer3 = Cash\n| length3 = 2:46\n\n| title4 = Don't Make Me Go\n| writer4 = Cash\n| length4 = 2:31\n\n| title5 = [[Guess Things Happen That Way]]\n| writer5 = Clement\n| length5 = 1:52\n\n| title6 = Train of Love\n| writer6 = Cash\n| length6 = 2:24\n\n| title7 = The Ways of a Woman in Love\n| writer7 = [[Bill Justis]], [[Charlie Rich]]\n| length7 = 2:16\n\n| title8 = Next in Line\n| writer8 = Cash\n| length8 = 2:49\n\n| title9 = You're the Nearest Thing to Heaven\n| writer9 = Jim Atkins, Cash, Hoyt Johnson\n| length9 = 2:42\n\n| title10 = I Can't Help It\n| writer10 = [[Hank Williams]]\n| length10 = 1:49\n\n| title11 = [[Home of the Blues]]\n| writer11 = Cash, Douglas Glenn Tubb, Lillie McAlpin\n| length11 = 2:41\n\n| title12 = [[Big River (Johnny Cash song)|Big River]]\n| writer12 = Cash\n| length12 = 2:35\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Re-issue Bonus tracks\n| writer_credits = yes\n| collapsed = yes\n| total_length = 38:08\n\n| title13 = Don't Make Me Go\n| writer13 = Cash\n| length13 = 2:30\n\n| title14 = The Ways of a Woman in Love\n| writer14 = Justis, Rich\n| length14= 2:28\n\n| title15 = Ballad of a Teenage Queen\n| writer15 = Clement\n| length15 = 2:15\n\n| title16 = Guess Things Happen That Way\n| writer16 = Clement\n| length16 = 1:58\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n*Johnny Cash&nbsp;\u2014 Vocals, acoustic Guitar and main performer\n*[[Luther Perkins]] - Guitar\n*[[Marshall Grant]] - Bass\n\n\n;TECHNICAL CREW\n*[[Sam Phillips]] - Producer\n*[[Jack Clement]] - Producer\n*Cary E. Mansfield&nbsp;\u2014 Reissue Producer\n*Bill Dahl&nbsp;\u2014 Liner Notes, Reissue Producer\n*Dan Hersch&nbsp;\u2014 Digital Remastering\n*Bill Pitzonka&nbsp;\u2014 Reissue Art Director\n\n==Charts==\n'''Singles''' - [[Billboard magazine|Billboard]] (North America)\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Year\n!align=\"left\"|Single\n!align=\"left\"|Chart\n!align=\"left\"|Position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1956\n|align=\"left\"|\"There You Go\"\n|align=\"left\"|Country Singles\n|align=\"left\"|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1957\n|align=\"left\"|\"Don't Make Me Go\"\n|align=\"left\"|Country Singles\n|align=\"left\"|9\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1957\n|align=\"left\"|\"Home of the Blues\"\n|align=\"left\"|Country Singles\n|align=\"left\"|3\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1957\n|align=\"left\"|\"Home of the Blues\"\n|align=\"left\"|Pop Singles\n|align=\"left\"|88\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1957\n|align=\"left\"|\"Next in Line\"\n|align=\"left\"|Country Singles\n|align=\"left\"|9\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1957\n|align=\"left\"|\"Next in Line\"\n