ferenced popular music videos including, [[BTS (band)|BTS]]'s \"[[Idol (BTS song)|Idol]]\", [[Marshmello]] and [[Bastille (band)|Bastille]]'s \"[[Happier (Marshmello and Bastille song)|Happier]]\", [[Kanye West]] and [[Lil Pump]]'s \"[[I Love It (Kanye West and Lil Pump song)|I Love It]]\", [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]'s \"In My Feelings\", [[El Chombo]]'s \"[[Dame Tu Cosita]]\", and [[Pinkfong]]'s \"[[Baby Shark]]\".\n\nAs of December 13, 2018, Everyone Controls Rewind became the most disliked video on the platform,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/youtube-rewind-2018-most-disliked-video-ever-1203088810/ |title=YouTube Rewind 2018 Officially Becomes Most-Disliked Video Ever |last=Spangler |first=Todd  |date=2018-12-13 |website=Variety |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181213183839/https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/youtube-rewind-2018-most-disliked-video-ever-1203088810/ |archive-date=December 13, 2018 |access-date=2019-04-27}}</ref> surpassing the previous holder of the title, \"[[Baby (Justin Bieber song)|Baby]]\" by [[Justin Bieber]]. Everyone Controls Rewind is also the first video to surpass ten million dislikes (December 2018), and 16 million dislikes (March 2019).\n\n;Appearances of YouTube personalities and special guests<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.portal-a.com/youtube-rewind-2018-everyone-controls-rewind/ |title=YouTube Rewind 2018: Everyone Controls Rewind {{!}} |website=www.portal-a.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181209124131/https://www.portal-a.com/youtube-rewind-2018-everyone-controls-rewind/ |archive-date=December 9, 2018 |access-date=December 7, 2018}}</ref>\nNotable YouTube creators featured in the video include:<ref name=\"YTRewind2018Creators\">''Replaced'': {{Cite web |url=https://rewind.youtube/creators |title=Rewind 2018 {{!}} Creators |website=Rewind 2018 |language=en |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181208162124/h