da (Nicki Minaj song)|Anaconda]]\" (Nicki Minaj) and \"[[Dark Horse (Katy Perry song)|Dark Horse\"]] (Katy Perry); and the game of the year, ''[[Flappy Bird]]''.\n\nThe music was mixed by DJ Earworm:\n*\"Turn Down for What\" by [[DJ Snake]] and [[Lil Jon]]\n*\"Fancy\" by [[Iggy Azalea]] feat. [[Charli XCX]]\n*\"Happy\" by [[Pharrell Williams]]\n*\"[[Bang Bang (Jessie J, Ariana Grande and Nicki Minaj song)|Bang Bang]]\" by [[Jessie J]], [[Ariana Grande]] & [[Nicki Minaj]]\n*\"[[All About That Bass]]\" by [[Meghan Trainor]]\n*\"[[Shake It Off (Taylor Swift song)|Shake It Off]]\" by [[Taylor Swift]]\n*\"[[Let It Go (Disney song)|Let It Go]]\" by [[Idina Menzel]] from ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]''\n\n;Appearances of YouTube personalities and special guests: (Italicized means uncredited) [[Action Movie Kid]], Adam Dahlberg (SkyDoesMinecraft), ''[[:jp:\u5927\u91ce\u611b\u5730|Aichi Ono]]'', [[Amanda Steele]] (MakeupByMandy24), Andy Raconte, Apollos Hester, [[Barely Productions]] (Barely Political), [[Bart Baker]], [[Bethany Mota]], Brett Nichols, [[:ja:\u5409\u7530\u3061\u304b|Chika Yoshida]], [[Chris Hardwick]], [[Colin Furze]], [[Conan O'Brien]], [[Conchita Wurst]], [[Corridor Digital]], [[Cyprien]], [[Dan Howell]] (danisnotonfire), [[Dodie Clark]], [[:fr:EnjoyPhoenix|EnjoyPhoenix]], [[Epic Rap Battles of History]], [[Evan Edinger]], [[Felix Kjellberg]] (PewDiePie), [[Fine Brothers Entertainment]] (The Fine Bros), [[:de:LeFloid|Florian Mundt]] (LeFloid), [[fouseyTUBE]], [[Freddie Wong]], [[Gabriel Valenciano]], [[Germ\u00e1n Garmendia]] (HolaSoyGerman), [[Grace Helbig]], ''[[:ja:\u306f\u3058\u3081\u3057\u3083\u3061\u3087\u30fc|hajimesyacho]]'', [[Hannah Hart]], [[Hikaru Kaihatsu]] (Hikakin), [[Ingrid Nilsen]], [[Jake Roper]], [[Jenna Mourey]], [[Jimmy Kimmel]], [[John Oliver]], [[Justine Ezarik]] (iJustine), [[Kevin Lieber]], [[Kid President]], [[King Russell]] (Kingsley), [[Kurt Hugo Schneider]], [[Lilly Singh]] ||Superwoman||, [[:jp:\u6751\u4e95\u667a\u5efa|Max Murai]], Matt Bittner, [[Michelle Phan]], Nilam Farooq (daaruum), [[Pentatonix]], [[Phil Lester]], [[PrankvsPrank]], [[Rhett and Link]], [[Rosanna Pansino]], Sadie Miller, [[Sam Tsui]], [[:de:Sami Slimani|Sami Slimani]], [[Sesame Street]] (Big Bird), Sir Fedora, [[Smosh]], [[Stephen Colbert]], [[Steve Kardynal]], [[Stuart Edge]], Tiny Hamster, [[The Gregory Brothers]], [[The Slow Mo Guys]], [[Troye Sivan]], [[Tyler Oakley]], [[vlogbrothers]], [[Vsauce2]] (Kevin Lieber), [[Vsauce3]] ([[Jake Roper]]), and [[World Order (band)|World Order]]\n}}\n<!-- YouTube Rewind 2015 -->\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = {{vanchor|YouTube Rewind: Now Watch Me 2015|YouTube Rewind: Now Watch Me 2015}}\n |Aux2            = 6:40\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|12|9}}\n |Aux4            = 145.90\n |LineColor       = 13599F\n |ShortSummary    = On December 9, 2015, YouTube Spotlight released \"Now Watch Me 2015\". The title refers to [[Silent\u00f3]]'s song \"[[Watch Me (Whip/Nae Nae)]]\". The video featured celebrities from 129 YouTube channels.\n\nEvents, headlining topics and viral videos of 2015 were references, including the [[Obergefell v. Hodges|legality of same-sex marriage in the U.S.]], [[Shia LaBeouf]]'s \"JUST DO IT!\" clips, [[Back to the Future]], Super Bowl [[Left Shark]], [[Kung Fury]], the [[Five Nights at Freddy's (series)|''Five Nights at Freddy's'' games]] (the game of the year), [[Rats in New York City|Pizza Rat]],<ref>{{Citation |last=Matt Little |title=New York City rat taking pizza home on the subway (Pizza Rat) |date=September 21, 2015 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UPXUG8q4jKU |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410010457/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UPXUG8q4jKU |access-date=April 10, 2016 |archive-date=April 10, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Carpool Karaoke]] and [[The dress (viral phenomenon)|the blue and black / white and gold dress]]. The following music videos were referenced: \"[[Cheerleader (song)|Cheerleader]]\" ([[Omi (singer)|OMI]]), \"[[Watch Me (Whip/Nae Nae)]]\" ([[Silent\u00f3]]), \"[[Lean On]]\" ([[Major Lazer]] & [[DJ Snake]] feat. [[M\u00d8]]), \"[[Hey Mama (David Guetta song)|Hey Mama]]\" ([[David Guetta]] feat. [[Nicki Minaj]], [[Afrojack]] and [[Bebe Rexha]]), \"[[Elastic Heart]]\" ([[Sia Furler|Sia]] feat. [[The Weeknd]] and [[Diplo]]), \"[[Hotline Bling]]\" ([[Drake (musician)|Drake]]) and \"[[What Do You Mean]] ([[Justin Bieber]]).\n\nSince 2015 was YouTube's tenth year of existence, viral videos from the whole of YouTube's span were included: The [[Ice Bucket Challenge]] in 2014, \"Volvo Trucks - The Epic Split feat. Van Damme (Live Test)\" in 2013,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M7FIvfx5J10&index=6&list=PLSTz8jpJdr5pn9LFw-pXbg0IOFy2Z_td_ Volvo Trucks - The Epic Split feat. Van Damme (Live Test)]</ref> Felix Baumgartner's supersonic freefall from 128k' - Mission Highlights in 2012, Rebecca Black's viral hit \"Friday\" in 2011, [[Double Rainbow (viral video)|Paul Vasquez's \"Double Rainbow]] in 2010, \"[[JK Wedding Entrance Dance]]\" in 2009, \"[[I'm on a Boat]]\" by [[the Lonely Island]] in 2009, \"[[Charlie Bit My Finger]]\" in 2007, [[Diet Coke and Mentos eruption|Diet Coke + Mentos]] and [[Judson Laipply]]'s viral video [[Judson Laipply|\"Evolution of Dance\"]] in 2006.\n\nThe music was composed by The Hood Internet with [[Avicii]]:\n*\"[[Cheerleader (song)|Cheerleader]]\" by [[Omi (singer)|OMI]] (feat. [[Felix Jaehn]])\n*\"[[What Do You Mean?]]\" by [[Justin Bieber]]\n*\"[[Watch Me (Whip/Nae Nae)]]\" by [[Silent\u00f3]]\n*\"[[Can't Feel My Face (The Weeknd song)|Can't Feel My Face]]\" by [[The Weeknd]]\n*\"[[Lean On]]\" by [[Major Lazer]] x DJ Snake feat. [[M\u00d8]]\n*\"[[Broken Arrows (song)|Broken Arrows]]\" by Avicii\n\n;Appearances of YouTube personalities and special guests:\nJenna Marbles, [[Lilly Singh]], [[Anna Akana]], [[Gigi Gorgeous]], [[Flula Borg]], [[Zoella]], [[Alfie Deyes|PointlessBlog]], [[Jenn McAllister]], [[Kingsley (YouTube)|Kingsley]], Grace Helbig, Hannah Hart, [[Mamrie Hart]], [[iJustine]], [[CaptainSparklez]], [[Timothy DeLaGhetto]], [[Todrick Hall]], [[PewDiePie]], [[Markiplier]], [[MatPat|The Game Theorists]], iHasCupquake, Hola Soy German, [[Enchufetv]], [[SQ/200|elrubiusOMG]], [[PrankvsPrank]], GloZell 006600, [[Ingrid Nilsen]], Tyler Oakley, [[Joey Graceffa]], fouseyTUBE, [[Adande Thorne|sWooZie]], Bart Baker, Smosh, SmoshGames, [[Rosanna Pansino]], [[Colleen Evans]] as [[Miranda Sings]], [[AmazingPhil]], [[Dan Howell|Daniel Howell]], MyLifeAsEva, Rhett and Link, the Fine Brothers, [[John Oliver]], Brizzy Voices, Heaven King, Johanna Colon, [[Sophia Grace & Rosie|Sophia Grace Brownlee]], Judson Laipply, [[Cameron Dallas]], [[Omi (singer)|OMI]], Jesse-Jane McParland, Cyprien and Norman.\n}}\n<!-- YouTube Rewind 2016 -->\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = {{vanchor|YouTube Rewind: The Ultimate 2016 Challenge|YouTube Rewind: The Ultimate 2016 Challenge}}\n |Aux2            = 6:53\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|12|7}}\n |Aux4            = 228.81\n |LineColor       = 13599F\n |ShortSummary    = On December 7, 2016, this video included references to events, headlining topics, viral videos and challenges of 2016. \"YouTube Rewind: The Ultimate 2016 Challenge\" became the fastest video to reach 100 million views on YouTube, just 3.2 days after its release.\n\nReferences included [[PPAP (Pen-Pineapple-Apple-Pen)|PPAP]], [[Dab (dance)|dabbing]], [[Mannequin Challenge]], [[2016 Summer Olympics|Rio 2016 Olympics]], [[water bottle flipping]], ''[[Stranger Things (TV series)|Stranger Things]]'', hydraulic press, Orbeeze pranks, Corn Drills, rainbow bagels, Scott Sterling, NYC snowboarding, [[Running Man Challenge]], [[Damn Daniel]], T-Rex costume, E-Games, The Dancing Mannequin Heads, [[The Door (Game of Thrones)|\"The Door\" (''Game of Thrones'')]], [[Prince (musician)|Prince]] and [[David Bowie]] Tribute