ou]]. This video included references to events, headlining topics, viral videos and challenges throughout the year. The video made cultural references to various trends in 2017, including the [[BBC News]] footage of [[Robert Kelly (political analyst)#BBC interview (2017)|a professor's children gatecrashing during a live interview]], [[fidget spinner]]s, the viral video of a train slamming into snow, D.I.Y. slime,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mashable.com/2017/07/06/reels-diy-instagram-slime/#fEQ.00sKIsqn |title=D.I.Y. slime |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207015513/http://mashable.com/2017/07/06/reels-diy-instagram-slime/#fEQ.00sKIsqn |archive-date=December 7, 2017 |access-date=December 6, 2017}}</ref> [[Salt Bae]], [[Solar eclipse of August 21, 2017|the 2017 solar eclipse]], [[Backpack Kid]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/05/21/backpack-kid-katy-perry-saturday-night-live/101988454/ |title=backpack kid |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171220063004/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/05/21/backpack-kid-katy-perry-saturday-night-live/101988454/ |archive-date=December 20, 2017 |access-date=December 6, 2017}}</ref> [[The floor is lava|the Floor is Lava challenge]], [[Man's Not Hot]], [[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|''Riverdale'']], the 1000\u02da knife, the song [[Shooting Stars (Bag Raiders song)#Revival|Shooting Stars]], the film [[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|''Wonder Woman'']], the controversy over the album cover of Ariana Grande's ''[[My Everything (Ariana Grande album)#Critical reception|''My Everything'']]'', the [[Hot Chicken Flavor Ramen|Fire Noodle Challenge]], April the&nbsp;Giraffe, Slime fight, Full face, the Rolex Challenge, and the film ''[[Get Out]]''. It also touched on various tragedies including [[Hurricane Harvey]], the [[Manchester Arena bombing]] and [[2017 Chiapas earthquake|Chiapas]] or [[2017 Central Mexico earthquake|Central Mexico 